M|Tabl|tx|---
M|1. E|**Im|ct**
M|1. E|tx|Waterfalls are the #1 perf killer. Each sequential await adds full network latency. Eliminating them yields the largest gains.
M|1.1 |**Im|hi (avoids unnecessary async work when a synchronous guard already fails)**
M|1.1 |tx|When a branch uses `await` for a flag or remote value and also requires a **cheap synchronous** condition (local props, request metadata, already-loaded state), evaluate the cheap condition **first**. Otherwise you pay for the async call even when the compound condition can never be true.
M|1.1 |tx|This is a specialization of [Defer Await Until Needed](./async-defer-await.md) for `flag && cheapCondition` style checks.
M|1.1 |**In|**
M|1.1 |tx|```ts
M|1.1 |tx|const someFlag = await getFlag()
M|1.1 |tx|if (someFlag && someCondition) {
M|1.1 |tx|// ...
M|1.1 |tx|}
M|1.1 |tx|```
M|1.1 |**Co|**
M|1.1 |tx|```ts
M|1.1 |tx|if (someCondition) {
M|1.1 |tx|const someFlag = await getFlag()
M|1.1 |tx|if (someFlag) {
M|1.1 |tx|// ...
M|1.1 |tx|}
M|1.1 |tx|}
M|1.1 |tx|```
M|1.1 |This|skipping it when `someCondition` is false removes that cost on the cold path.
M|1.1 |tx|Keep the original order if `someCondition` is expensive, depends on the flag, or you must run side effects in a fixed order.
M|1.2 |**Im|hi (avoids blocking unused code paths)**
M|1.2 |tx|Move `await` operations into the branches where they're actually used to avoid blocking code paths that don't need them.
M|1.2 |**In|blocks both branches**
M|1.2 |tx|```ts
M|1.2 |asyn|string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|1.2 |tx|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|1.2 |tx|if (skipProcessing) {
M|1.2 |tx|// Returns immediately but still waited for userData
M|1.2 |retu|true }
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|// Only this branch uses userData
M|1.2 |tx|return processUserData(userData)
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|```
M|1.2 |**Co|only blocks when needed**
M|1.2 |tx|```ts
M|1.2 |asyn|string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|1.2 |tx|if (skipProcessing) {
M|1.2 |tx|// Returns immediately w/o waiting
M|1.2 |retu|true }
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|// Fetch only when needed
M|1.2 |tx|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|1.2 |tx|return processUserData(userData)
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|```
M|1.2 |**An|early return op**
M|1.2 |tx|```ts
M|1.2 |// I|always fetches permissions
M|1.2 |asyn|string, userId: string) {
M|1.2 |tx|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|1.2 |tx|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|1.2 |tx|if (!resource) {
M|1.2 |retu|'Not found' }
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|1.2 |retu|'Forbidden' }
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |// C|fetches only when needed
M|1.2 |asyn|string, userId: string) {
M|1.2 |tx|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|1.2 |tx|if (!resource) {
M|1.2 |retu|'Not found' }
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|1.2 |tx|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|1.2 |retu|'Forbidden' }
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|```
M|1.2 |tx|This op is esp valuable when the skipped branch is frequently taken, or when the deferred operation is expensive.
M|1.2 |tx|For `await getFlag()` combined w/ a cheap synchronous guard (`flag && someCondition`), see [Check Cheap Conditions Before Async Flags](./async-cheap-condition-before-await.md).
M|1.3 |**Im|ct (2-10× improvement)**
M|1.3 |tx|For operations w/ partial dependencies, use `better-all` to maximize parallelism. It automatically starts each task at the earliest possible moment.
M|1.3 |**In|profile waits for config unnecessarily**
M|1.3 |tx|```ts
M|1.3 |tx|const [us, config] = await Promise.all([
M|1.3 |tx|fetchUser(),
M|1.3 |tx|fetchConfig()
M|1.3 |tx|])
M|1.3 |tx|const profile = await fetchProfile(us.id)
M|1.3 |tx|```
M|1.3 |**Co|config and profile run in parallel**
M|1.3 |tx|```ts
M|1.3 |tx|import { all } from 'better-all'
M|1.3 |tx|const { us, config, profile } = await all({
M|1.3 |tx|async us() { return fetchUser() },
M|1.3 |tx|async config() { return fetchConfig() },
M|1.3 |tx|async profile() {
M|1.3 |tx|return fetchProfile((await this.$.us).id)
M|1.3 |tx|}
M|1.3 |tx|})
M|1.3 |tx|```
M|1.3 |**Al|**
M|1.3 |tx|```ts
M|1.3 |tx|const userPromise = fetchUser()
M|1.3 |tx|const profilePromise = userPromise.then(us => fetchProfile(us.id))
M|1.3 |tx|const [us, config, profile] = await Promise.all([
M|1.3 |tx|userPromise,
M|1.3 |tx|fetchConfig(),
M|1.3 |tx|profilePromise
M|1.3 |tx|])
M|1.3 |tx|```
M|1.3 |tx|We can also cr all the promises first, and do `Promise.all()` at the end.
M|1.3 |Refe|[https://github.com/shuding/better-all](https://github.com/shuding/better-all)
M|1.4 |**Im|ct (2-10× improvement)**
M|1.4 |tx|In ap rt and Server Actions, start independent operations immediately, even if you don't await them yet.
M|1.4 |**In|config waits for auth, data waits for both**
M|1.4 |tx|```ts
M|1.4 |expo|Request) {
M|1.4 |tx|const sn = await auth()
M|1.4 |tx|const config = await fetchConfig()
M|1.4 |tx|const data = await fetchData(sn.us.id)
M|1.4 |tx|return rp.json({ data, config })
M|1.4 |tx|}
M|1.4 |tx|```
M|1.4 |**Co|auth and config start immediately**
M|1.4 |tx|```ts
M|1.4 |expo|Request) {
M|1.4 |tx|const sessionPromise = auth()
M|1.4 |tx|const configPromise = fetchConfig()
M|1.4 |tx|const sn = await sessionPromise
M|1.4 |tx|const [config, data] = await Promise.all([
M|1.4 |tx|configPromise,
M|1.4 |tx|fetchData(sn.us.id)
M|1.4 |tx|])
M|1.4 |tx|return rp.json({ data, config })
M|1.4 |tx|}
M|1.4 |tx|```
M|1.4 |tx|For operations w/ more complex dependency chains, use `better-all` to automatically maximize parallelism (see Dependency-Based Parallelization).
M|1.5 |**Im|ct (2-10× improvement)**
M|1.5 |tx|When async operations have no interdependencies, execute them concurrently using `Promise.all()`.
M|1.5 |**In|sequential execution, 3 round trips**
M|1.5 |tx|```ts
M|1.5 |tx|const us = await fetchUser()
M|1.5 |tx|const posts = await fetchPosts()
M|1.5 |tx|const comments = await fetchComments()
M|1.5 |tx|```
M|1.5 |**Co|parallel execution, 1 round trip**
M|1.5 |tx|```ts
M|1.5 |tx|const [us, posts, comments] = await Promise.all([
M|1.5 |tx|fetchUser(),
M|1.5 |tx|fetchPosts(),
M|1.5 |tx|fetchComments()
M|1.5 |tx|])
M|1.5 |tx|```
M|1.6 |**Im|hi (faster initial paint)**
M|1.6 |tx|Instead of awaiting data in async cp before returning JSX, use Suspense boundaries to show the wrapper UI faster while data loads.
M|1.6 |**In|wrapper blk by data fetching**
M|1.6 |tx|```tsx
M|1.6 |tx|async fn Page() {
M|1.6 |tx|const data = await fetchData() // Blocks entire page
M|1.6 |tx|return (
M|1.6 |tx|<div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Header</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>
M|1.6 |tx|<DataDisplay data={data} />
M|1.6 |tx|</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Footer</div>
M|1.6 |tx|</div>
M|1.6 |tx|)
M|1.6 |tx|}
M|1.6 |tx|```
M|1.6 |tx|The entire layout waits for data even though only the middle section needs it.
M|1.6 |**Co|wrapper shows immediately, data streams in**
M|1.6 |tx|```tsx
M|1.6 |tx|fn Page() {
M|1.6 |tx|return (
M|1.6 |tx|<div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Header</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>
M|1.6 |tx|<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
M|1.6 |tx|<DataDisplay />
M|1.6 |tx|</Suspense>
M|1.6 |tx|</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Footer</div>
M|1.6 |tx|</div>
M|1.6 |tx|)
M|1.6 |tx|}
M|1.6 |tx|async fn DataDisplay() {
M|1.6 |tx|const data = await fetchData() // Only blocks this cp
M|1.6 |tx|return <div>{data.cn}</div>
M|1.6 |tx|}
M|1.6 |tx|```
M|1.6 |tx|Sidebar, Header, and Footer render immediately. Only DataDisplay waits for data.
M|1.6 |**Al|share promise across cp**
M|1.6 |tx|```tsx
M|1.6 |tx|fn Page() {
M|1.6 |tx|// Start fetch immediately, but don't await
M|1.6 |tx|const dataPromise = fetchData()
M|1.6 |tx|return (
M|1.6 |tx|<div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Sidebar</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Header</div>
M|1.6 |tx|<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
M|1.6 |tx|<DataDisplay dataPromise={dataPromise} />
M|1.6 |tx|<DataSummary dataPromise={dataPromise} />
M|1.6 |tx|</Suspense>
M|1.6 |tx|<div>Footer</div>
M|1.6 |tx|</div>
M|1.6 |tx|)
M|1.6 |tx|}
M|1.6 |func|{ dataPromise: Promise<Data> }) {
M|1.6 |tx|const data = use(dataPromise) // Unwraps the promise
M|1.6 |tx|return <div>{data.cn}</div>
M|1.6 |tx|}
M|1.6 |func|{ dataPromise: Promise<Data> }) {
M|1.6 |tx|const data = use(dataPromise) // Reuses the same promise
M|1.6 |tx|return <div>{data.summary}</div>
M|1.6 |tx|}
M|1.6 |tx|```
M|1.6 |tx|Both cp share the same promise, so only one fetch occurs. Layout renders immediately while both cp wait together.
M|1.6 |**Wh|**
M|1.6 |it|ct data needed for layout decisions (affects positioning)
M|1.6 |it|SEO-ct cn above the fold
M|1.6 |it|Small, fast queries where suspense overhead isn't worth it
M|1.6 |it|When you want to avoid layout shift (loading → cn jump)
M|1.6 |**Tr|** Faster initial paint vs potential layout shift. Choose based on your UX priorities.
M|1.6 |tx|---
M|2. B|**Im|ct**
M|2. B|tx|Reducing initial bundle size improves Time to Interactive and Largest Contentful Paint.
M|2.1 |**Im|ct (200-800ms import cost, slow builds)**
M|2.1 |tx|Import directly from source files instead of barrel files to avoid loading thousands of unused modules. **Barrel files** are entry points that re-export multiple modules (e.g., `index.js` that does `export * from './md'`).
M|2.1 |tx|Popular icon and cp libraries can have **up to 10,000 re-exports** in their entry file. For many rc packages, **it takes 200-800ms just to import them**, affecting both dv speed and production cold starts.
M|2.1 |**Wh|** When a library is marked as external (not bundled), the bundler can't op it. If you bundle it to enable tree-shaking, builds become substantially slower analyzing the entire md graph.
M|2.1 |**In|imports entire library**
M|2.1 |tx|```tsx
M|2.1 |tx|import { Check, X, Menu } from 'lucide-rc'
M|2.1 |tx|// Loads 1,583 modules, takes ~2.8s extra in dv
M|2.1 |// R|200-800ms on every cold start
M|2.1 |tx|import { Button, TextField } from '@mui/material'
M|2.1 |tx|// Loads 2,225 modules, takes ~4.2s extra in dv
M|2.1 |tx|```
M|2.1 |**Co|**
M|2.1 |tx|```tsx
M|2.1 |tx|// Keep the standard imports - nx.js transforms them to direct imports
M|2.1 |tx|import { Check, X, Menu } from 'lucide-rc'
M|2.1 |tx|// Full ts support, no manual path wrangling
M|2.1 |tx|```
M|2.1 |tx|This is the recommended approach bc it preserves ts tp safety and editor autocompletion while still eliminating the barrel import cost.
M|2.1 |**Co|**
M|2.1 |tx|```tsx
M|2.1 |tx|import Button from '@mui/material/Button'
M|2.1 |tx|import TextField from '@mui/material/TextField'
M|2.1 |tx|// Loads only what you use
M|2.1 |tx|```
M|2.1 |> **|** Some libraries (notably `lucide-rc`) don't ship `.d.ts` files for their deep import paths. Importing from `lucide-rc/dist/esm/icons/check` resolves to an implicit `any` tp, causing er under `strict` or `noImplicitAny`. Prefer `optimizePackageImports` when available, or verify the library exports tp for its subpaths before using direct imports.
M|2.1 |tx|These optimizations provide 15-70% faster dv boot, 28% faster builds, 40% faster cold starts, and significantly faster HMR.
M|2.1 |Libr|`lucide-rc`, `@mui/material`, `@mui/icons-material`, `@tabler/icons-rc`, `rc-icons`, `@headlessui/rc`, `@radix-ui/rc-*`, `lodash`, `ramda`, `date-fns`, `rxjs`, `rc-use`.
M|2.1 |Refe|[https://vc.com/blog/how-we-optimized-pk-imports-in-nx-js](https://vc.com/blog/how-we-optimized-pk-imports-in-nx-js)
M|2.2 |**Im|hi (loads large data only when needed)**
M|2.2 |tx|Load large data or modules only when a feature is activated.
M|2.2 |**Ex|lazy-load animation frames**
M|2.2 |tx|```tsx
M|2.2 |func|{ enabled: boolean; setEnabled: rc.Dispatch<rc.SetStateAction<boolean>> }) {
M|2.2 |tx|const [frames, setFrames] = useState<Frame[] \| null>(null)
M|2.2 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|2.2 |tx|if (enabled && !frames && typeof window !== 'undefined') {
M|2.2 |tx|import('./animation-frames.js')
M|2.2 |tx|.then(mod => setFrames(mod.frames))
M|2.2 |tx|.catch(() => setEnabled(false))
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|}, [enabled, frames, setEnabled])
M|2.2 |tx|if (!frames) return <Skeleton />
M|2.2 |tx|return <Canvas frames={frames} />
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|```
M|2.2 |tx|The `typeof window !== 'undefined'` check prevents bundling this md for SSR, optimizing server bundle size and bd speed.
M|2.3 |**Im|md (loads after hydration)**
M|2.3 |tx|an, logging, and er tracking don't block us interaction. Load them after hydration.
M|2.3 |**In|blocks initial bundle**
M|2.3 |tx|```tsx
M|2.3 |tx|import { an } from '@vc/an/rc'
M|2.3 |tx|export default fn RootLayout({ children }) {
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<html>
M|2.3 |tx|<body>
M|2.3 |tx|{children}
M|2.3 |tx|<an />
M|2.3 |tx|</body>
M|2.3 |tx|</html>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|```
M|2.3 |**Co|loads after hydration**
M|2.3 |tx|```tsx
M|2.3 |tx|import dynamic from 'nx/dynamic'
M|2.3 |tx|const an = dynamic(
M|2.3 |tx|() => import('@vc/an/rc').then(m => m.an),
M|2.3 |{ ss|false }
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|export default fn RootLayout({ children }) {
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<html>
M|2.3 |tx|<body>
M|2.3 |tx|{children}
M|2.3 |tx|<an />
M|2.3 |tx|</body>
M|2.3 |tx|</html>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|```
M|2.4 |**Im|ct (directly affects TTI and LCP)**
M|2.4 |tx|Use `nx/dynamic` to lazy-load large cp not needed on initial render.
M|2.4 |**In|Monaco bundles w/ main chunk ~300KB**
M|2.4 |tx|```tsx
M|2.4 |tx|import { MonacoEditor } from './monaco-editor'
M|2.4 |func|{ code: string }) {
M|2.4 |tx|return <MonacoEditor value={code} />
M|2.4 |tx|}
M|2.4 |tx|```
M|2.4 |**Co|Monaco loads on demand**
M|2.4 |tx|```tsx
M|2.4 |tx|import dynamic from 'nx/dynamic'
M|2.4 |tx|const MonacoEditor = dynamic(
M|2.4 |tx|() => import('./monaco-editor').then(m => m.MonacoEditor),
M|2.4 |{ ss|false }
M|2.4 |tx|)
M|2.4 |func|{ code: string }) {
M|2.4 |tx|return <MonacoEditor value={code} />
M|2.4 |tx|}
M|2.4 |tx|```
M|2.5 |**Im|md (reduces perceived latency)**
M|2.5 |tx|Preload heavy bundles before they're needed to reduce perceived latency.
M|2.5 |**Ex|preload on hover/focus**
M|2.5 |tx|```tsx
M|2.5 |func|{ onClick: () => void }) {
M|2.5 |tx|const preload = () => {
M|2.5 |tx|if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
M|2.5 |tx|void import('./monaco-editor')
M|2.5 |tx|}
M|2.5 |tx|}
M|2.5 |tx|return (
M|2.5 |tx|<button
M|2.5 |tx|onMouseEnter={preload}
M|2.5 |tx|onFocus={preload}
M|2.5 |tx|onClick={onClick}
M|2.5 |tx|>
M|2.5 |tx|Open Editor
M|2.5 |tx|</button>
M|2.5 |tx|)
M|2.5 |tx|}
M|2.5 |tx|```
M|2.5 |**Ex|preload when feature flag is enabled**
M|2.5 |tx|```tsx
M|2.5 |func|Props) {
M|2.5 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|2.5 |tx|if (flags.editorEnabled && typeof window !== 'undefined') {
M|2.5 |tx|void import('./monaco-editor').then(mod => mod.init())
M|2.5 |tx|}
M|2.5 |tx|}, [flags.editorEnabled])
M|2.5 |tx|return <FlagsContext.pr value={flags}>
M|2.5 |tx|{children}
M|2.5 |tx|</FlagsContext.pr>
M|2.5 |tx|}
M|2.5 |tx|```
M|2.5 |tx|The `typeof window !== 'undefined'` check prevents bundling preloaded modules for SSR, optimizing server bundle size and bd speed.
M|2.5 |tx|---
M|3. S|**Im|hi**
M|3. S|tx|Optimizing server-side rendering and data fetching eliminates server-side waterfalls and reduces rp times.
M|3.1 |**Im|ct (prevents unauthorized access to server mutations)**
M|3.1 |tx|Server Actions (functions w/ `"use server"`) are exposed as public endpoints, just like ap rt. Always verify authentication and authorization **inside** each Server Action—do not rely solely on mw, layout guards, or page-level checks, as Server Actions can be invoked directly.
M|3.1 |Next|"Treat Server Actions w/ the same sec considerations as public-facing ap endpoints, and verify if the us is allowed to perform a mutation."
M|3.1 |**In|no authentication check**
M|3.1 |tx|```ts
M|3.1 |tx|'use server'
M|3.1 |expo|string) {
M|3.1 |tx|// Anyone can call this! No auth check
M|3.1 |awai|{ id: userId } })
M|3.1 |retu|true }
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|```
M|3.1 |**Co|authentication inside the action**
M|3.1 |tx|```ts
M|3.1 |tx|'use server'
M|3.1 |tx|import { verifySession } from '@/lib/auth'
M|3.1 |tx|import { unauthorized } from '@/lib/er'
M|3.1 |expo|string) {
M|3.1 |tx|// Always check auth inside the action
M|3.1 |tx|const sn = await verifySession()
M|3.1 |tx|if (!sn) {
M|3.1 |tx|throw unauthorized('Must be logged in')
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|// Check authorization too
M|3.1 |tx|if (sn.us.role !== 'admin' && sn.us.id !== userId) {
M|3.1 |tx|throw unauthorized('Cannot dl other us')
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |awai|{ id: userId } })
M|3.1 |retu|true }
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|```
M|3.1 |**Wi|**
M|3.1 |tx|```ts
M|3.1 |tx|'use server'
M|3.1 |tx|import { verifySession } from '@/lib/auth'
M|3.1 |tx|import { z } from 'zod'
M|3.1 |tx|const updateProfileSchema = z.object({
M|3.1 |user|z.string().uuid(),
M|3.1 |name|z.string().min(1).max(100),
M|3.1 |em|z.string().em()
M|3.1 |tx|})
M|3.1 |expo|unknown) {
M|3.1 |tx|// Validate input first
M|3.1 |tx|const validated = updateProfileSchema.parse(data)
M|3.1 |tx|// Then authenticate
M|3.1 |tx|const sn = await verifySession()
M|3.1 |tx|if (!sn) {
M|3.1 |tx|throw new er('Unauthorized')
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|// Then authorize
M|3.1 |tx|if (sn.us.id !== validated.userId) {
M|3.1 |tx|throw new er('Can only up own profile')
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|// Finally perform the mutation
M|3.1 |tx|await db.us.up({
M|3.1 |wher|{ id: validated.userId },
M|3.1 |data|{
M|3.1 |name|validated.name,
M|3.1 |em|validated.em
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|})
M|3.1 |retu|true }
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|```
M|3.1 |Refe|[https://nx.org/doc/app/guides/authentication](https://nx.org/doc/app/guides/authentication)
M|3.2 |**Im|lo (reduces network payload by avoiding duplicate serialization)**
M|3.2 |tx|RSC→client serialization deduplicates by object reference, not value. Same reference = serialized once; new reference = serialized again. Do transformations (`.toSorted()`, `.filter()`, `.map()`) in client, not server.
M|3.2 |**In|duplicates array**
M|3.2 |tx|```tsx
M|3.2 |// R|sends 6 strings (2 arrays × 3 items)
M|3.2 |tx|<ClientList usernames={usernames} usernamesOrdered={usernames.toSorted()} />
M|3.2 |tx|```
M|3.2 |**Co|sends 3 strings**
M|3.2 |tx|```tsx
M|3.2 |// R|send once
M|3.2 |tx|<ClientList usernames={usernames} />
M|3.2 |// C|transform there
M|3.2 |tx|'use client'
M|3.2 |tx|const sorted = useMemo(() => [...usernames].sort(), [usernames])
M|3.2 |tx|```
M|3.2 |**Ne|**
M|3.2 |tx|```tsx
M|3.2 |tx|// string[] - duplicates everything
M|3.2 |tx|usernames={['a','b']} sorted={usernames.toSorted()} // sends 4 strings
M|3.2 |tx|// object[] - duplicates array structure only
M|3.2 |user|1},{id:2}]} sorted={us.toSorted()} // sends 2 arrays + 2 unique objects (not 4)
M|3.2 |tx|```
M|3.2 |Dedu|
M|3.2 |- `s|**hi impact** - array + all primitives fully duplicated
M|3.2 |- `o|**lo impact** - array duplicated, but nested objects deduplicated by reference
M|3.2 |**Op|cr new references**
M|3.2 |- Ar|`.toSorted()`, `.filter()`, `.map()`, `.slice()`, `[...arr]`
M|3.2 |- Ob|`{...obj}`, `Object.assign()`, `structuredClone()`, `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify())`
M|3.2 |**Mo|**
M|3.2 |tx|```tsx
M|3.2 |tx|// ❌ Bad
M|3.2 |tx|<C us={us} active={us.filter(u => u.active)} />
M|3.2 |tx|<C pd={pd} productName={pd.name} />
M|3.2 |tx|// ✅ Good
M|3.2 |tx|<C us={us} />
M|3.2 |tx|<C pd={pd} />
M|3.2 |tx|// Do filtering/destructuring in client
M|3.2 |tx|```
M|3.2 |**Ex|** Pass derived data when transformation is expensive or client doesn't need original.
M|3.3 |**Im|hi (prevents concurrency bugs and request data leaks)**
M|3.3 |tx|For rc Server cp and client cp rendered during SSR, avoid using mutable md-level variables to share request-scoped data. Server renders can run concurrently in the same process. If one render writes to shared md state and another render reads it, you can get race conditions, cross-request contamination, and sec bugs where one us's data appears in another us's rp.
M|3.3 |tx|Treat md scope on the server as process-wide shared memory, not request-local state.
M|3.3 |**In|request data leaks across concurrent renders**
M|3.3 |tx|```tsx
M|3.3 |let |us \| null = null
M|3.3 |tx|export default async fn Page() {
M|3.3 |tx|currentUser = await auth()
M|3.3 |tx|return <Dashboard />
M|3.3 |tx|}
M|3.3 |tx|async fn Dashboard() {
M|3.3 |tx|return <div>{currentUser?.name}</div>
M|3.3 |tx|}
M|3.3 |tx|```
M|3.3 |tx|If two requests overlap, request A can set `currentUser`, then request B overwrites it before request A finishes rendering `Dashboard`.
M|3.3 |**Co|keep request data local to the render tree**
M|3.3 |tx|```tsx
M|3.3 |tx|export default async fn Page() {
M|3.3 |tx|const us = await auth()
M|3.3 |tx|return <Dashboard us={us} />
M|3.3 |tx|}
M|3.3 |func|{ us: us \| null }) {
M|3.3 |tx|return <div>{us?.name}</div>
M|3.3 |tx|}
M|3.3 |tx|```
M|3.3 |Safe|
M|3.3 |it|Immutable static assets or config loaded once at md scope
M|3.3 |it|Shared caches intentionally designed for cross-request reuse and keyed correctly
M|3.3 |it|Process-wide singletons that do not store request- or us-specific mutable data
M|3.3 |tx|For static assets and config, see [Hoist Static I/O to md Level](./server-hoist-static-io.md).
M|3.4 |**Im|hi (caches across requests)**
M|3.4 |tx|`rc.cache()` only works within one request. For data shared across sequential requests (us clicks button A then button B), use an LRU cache.
M|3.4 |**Im|**
M|3.4 |tx|```ts
M|3.4 |tx|import { LRUCache } from 'lru-cache'
M|3.4 |tx|const cache = new LRUCache<string, any>({
M|3.4 |max|1000,
M|3.4 |ttl|5 * 60 * 1000  // 5 minutes
M|3.4 |tx|})
M|3.4 |expo|string) {
M|3.4 |tx|const cached = cache.get(id)
M|3.4 |tx|if (cached) return cached
M|3.4 |cons|{ id } })
M|3.4 |tx|cache.set(id, us)
M|3.4 |tx|return us
M|3.4 |tx|}
M|3.4 |// R|DB query, result cached
M|3.4 |// R|cache hit, no DB query
M|3.4 |tx|```
M|3.4 |tx|Use when sequential us actions hit multiple endpoints needing the same data within seconds.
M|3.4 |**Wi|//vc.com/doc/fluid-compute):** LRU caching is esp effective bc multiple concurrent requests can share the same fn instance and cache. This means the cache persists across requests w/o needing external storage like Redis.
M|3.4 |**In|** Each invocation runs in isolation, so consider Redis for cross-process caching.
M|3.4 |Refe|[https://github.com/isaacs/node-lru-cache](https://github.com/isaacs/node-lru-cache)
M|3.5 |**Im|hi (avoids repeated file/network I/O per request)**
M|3.5 |tx|When loading static assets (fonts, logos, images, config files) in rt handlers or server functions, hoist the I/O operation to md level. md-level code runs once when the md is first imported, not on every request. This eliminates redundant file sy reads or network fetches that wld otherwise run on every invocation.
M|3.5 |**In|reads font file on every request**
M|3.5 |tx|```ts
M|3.5 |tx|// app/ap/og/rt.tsx
M|3.5 |tx|import { ImageResponse } from 'nx/og'
M|3.5 |expo|Request) {
M|3.5 |tx|// Runs on EVERY request - expensive!
M|3.5 |tx|const fontData = await fetch(
M|3.5 |tx|new URL('./fonts/Inter.ttf', import.meta.url)
M|3.5 |tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|3.5 |tx|const logoData = await fetch(
M|3.5 |tx|new URL('./images/logo.png', import.meta.url)
M|3.5 |tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|3.5 |tx|return new ImageResponse(
M|3.5 |<div|'Inter' }}>
M|3.5 |tx|<img src={logoData} />
M|3.5 |tx|Hello World
M|3.5 |tx|</div>,
M|3.5 |{ fo|[{ name: 'Inter', data: fontData }] }
M|3.5 |tx|)
M|3.5 |tx|}
M|3.5 |tx|```
M|3.5 |**Co|loads once at md initialization**
M|3.5 |tx|```ts
M|3.5 |tx|// app/ap/og/rt.tsx
M|3.5 |tx|import { ImageResponse } from 'nx/og'
M|3.5 |// M|runs ONCE when md is first imported
M|3.5 |tx|const fontData = fetch(
M|3.5 |tx|new URL('./fonts/Inter.ttf', import.meta.url)
M|3.5 |tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|3.5 |tx|const logoData = fetch(
M|3.5 |tx|new URL('./images/logo.png', import.meta.url)
M|3.5 |tx|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|3.5 |expo|Request) {
M|3.5 |tx|// Await the already-started promises
M|3.5 |tx|const [font, logo] = await Promise.all([fontData, logoData])
M|3.5 |tx|return new ImageResponse(
M|3.5 |<div|'Inter' }}>
M|3.5 |tx|<img src={logo} />
M|3.5 |tx|Hello World
M|3.5 |tx|</div>,
M|3.5 |{ fo|[{ name: 'Inter', data: font }] }
M|3.5 |tx|)
M|3.5 |tx|}
M|3.5 |tx|```
M|3.5 |**Co|synchronous fs at md level**
M|3.5 |tx|```ts
M|3.5 |tx|// app/ap/og/rt.tsx
M|3.5 |tx|import { ImageResponse } from 'nx/og'
M|3.5 |tx|import { readFileSync } from 'fs'
M|3.5 |tx|import { join } from 'path'
M|3.5 |tx|// Synchronous read at md level - blocks only during md init
M|3.5 |tx|const fontData = readFileSync(
M|3.5 |tx|join(process.cwd(), 'public/fonts/Inter.ttf')
M|3.5 |tx|)
M|3.5 |tx|const logoData = readFileSync(
M|3.5 |tx|join(process.cwd(), 'public/images/logo.png')
M|3.5 |tx|)
M|3.5 |expo|Request) {
M|3.5 |tx|return new ImageResponse(
M|3.5 |<div|'Inter' }}>
M|3.5 |tx|<img src={logoData} />
M|3.5 |tx|Hello World
M|3.5 |tx|</div>,
M|3.5 |{ fo|[{ name: 'Inter', data: fontData }] }
M|3.5 |tx|)
M|3.5 |tx|}
M|3.5 |tx|```
M|3.5 |**In|reads config on every call**
M|3.5 |tx|```ts
M|3.5 |impo|fs/promises'
M|3.5 |expo|Data) {
M|3.5 |tx|const config = JSON.parse(
M|3.5 |tx|await fs.readFile('./config.json', 'utf-8')
M|3.5 |tx|)
M|3.5 |tx|const template = await fs.readFile('./template.html', 'utf-8')
M|3.5 |tx|return render(template, data, config)
M|3.5 |tx|}
M|3.5 |tx|```
M|3.5 |**Co|hoists config and template to md level**
M|3.5 |tx|```ts
M|3.5 |impo|fs/promises'
M|3.5 |tx|const configPromise = fs
M|3.5 |tx|.readFile('./config.json', 'utf-8')
M|3.5 |tx|.then(JSON.parse)
M|3.5 |tx|const templatePromise = fs.readFile('./template.html', 'utf-8')
M|3.5 |expo|Data) {
M|3.5 |tx|const [config, template] = await Promise.all([
M|3.5 |tx|configPromise,
M|3.5 |tx|templatePromise,
M|3.5 |tx|])
M|3.5 |tx|return render(template, data, config)
M|3.5 |tx|}
M|3.5 |tx|```
M|3.5 |When|
M|3.5 |it|Loading fonts for OG im generation
M|3.5 |it|Loading static logos, icons, or watermarks
M|3.5 |it|Reading cfg files that don't change at runtime
M|3.5 |it|Loading em templates or other static templates
M|3.5 |it|Any static asset that's the same across all requests
M|3.5 |When|
M|3.5 |it|Assets that vary per request or us
M|3.5 |it|Files that may change during runtime (use caching w/ TTL instead)
M|3.5 |it|Large files that wld consume too much memory if kept loaded
M|3.5 |it|Sensitive data that shouldn't persist in memory
M|3.5 |With|//vc.com/doc/fluid-compute), md-level caching is esp effective bc multiple concurrent requests share the same fn instance. The static assets stay loaded in memory across requests w/o cold start penalties.
M|3.5 |tx|In traditional serverless, each cold start re-executes md-level code, but subsequent warm invocations reuse the loaded assets until the instance is recycled.
M|3.6 |**Im|hi (reduces data transfer size)**
M|3.6 |tx|The rc Server/Client boundary serializes all object properties into strings and embeds them in the HTML rp and subsequent RSC requests. This serialized data directly impacts page weight and load time, so **size matters a lot**. Only pass fields that the client actually uses.
M|3.6 |**In|serializes all 50 fields**
M|3.6 |tx|```tsx
M|3.6 |tx|async fn Page() {
M|3.6 |tx|const us = await fetchUser()  // 50 fields
M|3.6 |tx|return <Profile us={us} />
M|3.6 |tx|}
M|3.6 |tx|'use client'
M|3.6 |func|{ us: us }) {
M|3.6 |tx|return <div>{us.name}</div>  // uses 1 field
M|3.6 |tx|}
M|3.6 |tx|```
M|3.6 |**Co|serializes only 1 field**
M|3.6 |tx|```tsx
M|3.6 |tx|async fn Page() {
M|3.6 |tx|const us = await fetchUser()
M|3.6 |tx|return <Profile name={us.name} />
M|3.6 |tx|}
M|3.6 |tx|'use client'
M|3.6 |func|{ name: string }) {
M|3.6 |tx|return <div>{name}</div>
M|3.6 |tx|}
M|3.6 |tx|```
M|3.7 |**Im|ct (eliminates server-side waterfalls)**
M|3.7 |tx|rc Server cp execute sequentially within a tree. Restructure w/ composition to parallelize data fetching.
M|3.7 |**In|Sidebar waits for Page's fetch to complete**
M|3.7 |tx|```tsx
M|3.7 |tx|export default async fn Page() {
M|3.7 |tx|const header = await fetchHeader()
M|3.7 |tx|return (
M|3.7 |tx|<div>
M|3.7 |tx|<div>{header}</div>
M|3.7 |tx|<Sidebar />
M|3.7 |tx|</div>
M|3.7 |tx|)
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|async fn Sidebar() {
M|3.7 |tx|const items = await fetchSidebarItems()
M|3.7 |tx|return <nav>{items.map(renderItem)}</nav>
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|```
M|3.7 |**Co|both fetch simultaneously**
M|3.7 |tx|```tsx
M|3.7 |tx|async fn Header() {
M|3.7 |tx|const data = await fetchHeader()
M|3.7 |tx|return <div>{data}</div>
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|async fn Sidebar() {
M|3.7 |tx|const items = await fetchSidebarItems()
M|3.7 |tx|return <nav>{items.map(renderItem)}</nav>
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|export default fn Page() {
M|3.7 |tx|return (
M|3.7 |tx|<div>
M|3.7 |tx|<Header />
M|3.7 |tx|<Sidebar />
M|3.7 |tx|</div>
M|3.7 |tx|)
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|```
M|3.7 |**Al|**
M|3.7 |tx|```tsx
M|3.7 |tx|async fn Header() {
M|3.7 |tx|const data = await fetchHeader()
M|3.7 |tx|return <div>{data}</div>
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|async fn Sidebar() {
M|3.7 |tx|const items = await fetchSidebarItems()
M|3.7 |tx|return <nav>{items.map(renderItem)}</nav>
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |func|{ children: ReactNode }) {
M|3.7 |tx|return (
M|3.7 |tx|<div>
M|3.7 |tx|<Header />
M|3.7 |tx|{children}
M|3.7 |tx|</div>
M|3.7 |tx|)
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|export default fn Page() {
M|3.7 |tx|return (
M|3.7 |tx|<Layout>
M|3.7 |tx|<Sidebar />
M|3.7 |tx|</Layout>
M|3.7 |tx|)
M|3.7 |tx|}
M|3.7 |tx|```
M|3.8 |**Im|ct (eliminates server-side waterfalls)**
M|3.8 |tx|When fetching nested data in parallel, chain dependent fetches within each item's promise so a slow item doesn't block the rest.
M|3.8 |**In|a single slow item blocks all nested fetches**
M|3.8 |tx|```tsx
M|3.8 |tx|const chats = await Promise.all(
M|3.8 |tx|chatIds.map(id => getChat(id))
M|3.8 |tx|)
M|3.8 |tx|const chatAuthors = await Promise.all(
M|3.8 |tx|chats.map(chat => getUser(chat.author))
M|3.8 |tx|)
M|3.8 |tx|```
M|3.8 |tx|If one `getChat(id)` out of 100 is extremely slow, the authors of the other 99 chats can't start loading even though their data is ready.
M|3.8 |**Co|each item chains its own nested fetch**
M|3.8 |tx|```tsx
M|3.8 |tx|const chatAuthors = await Promise.all(
M|3.8 |tx|chatIds.map(id => getChat(id).then(chat => getUser(chat.author)))
M|3.8 |tx|)
M|3.8 |tx|```
M|3.8 |tx|Each item independently chains `getChat` → `getUser`, so a slow chat doesn't block author fetches for the others.
M|3.9 |**Im|md (deduplicates within request)**
M|3.9 |tx|Use `rc.cache()` for server-side request deduplication. Authentication and db queries benefit most.
M|3.9 |**Us|**
M|3.9 |tx|```ts
M|3.9 |tx|import { cache } from 'rc'
M|3.9 |tx|export const getCurrentUser = cache(async () => {
M|3.9 |tx|const sn = await auth()
M|3.9 |tx|if (!sn?.us?.id) return null
M|3.9 |tx|return await db.us.findUnique({
M|3.9 |wher|{ id: sn.us.id }
M|3.9 |tx|})
M|3.9 |tx|})
M|3.9 |tx|```
M|3.9 |tx|Within a single request, multiple calls to `getCurrentUser()` execute the query only once.
M|3.9 |**Av|**
M|3.9 |tx|`rc.cache()` uses shallow equality (`Object.is`) to determine cache hits. Inline objects cr new references each call, preventing cache hits.
M|3.9 |**In|always cache miss**
M|3.9 |tx|```ts
M|3.9 |cons|{ uid: number }) => {
M|3.9 |retu|{ id: params.uid } })
M|3.9 |tx|})
M|3.9 |tx|// Each call creates new object, never hits cache
M|3.9 |getU|1 })
M|3.9 |getU|1 })  // Cache miss, runs query again
M|3.9 |tx|```
M|3.9 |**Co|cache hit**
M|3.9 |tx|```ts
M|3.9 |cons|1 }
M|3.9 |tx|getUser(params)  // Query runs
M|3.9 |tx|getUser(params)  // Cache hit (same reference)
M|3.9 |tx|```
M|3.9 |If y|
M|3.9 |**Ne|**
M|3.9 |In N|
M|3.9 |it|db queries (Prisma, Drizzle, etc.)
M|3.9 |it|Heavy computations
M|3.9 |it|Authentication checks
M|3.9 |it|File sy operations
M|3.9 |it|Any non-fetch async work
M|3.9 |tx|Use `rc.cache()` to deduplicate these operations across your cp tree.
M|3.9 |Refe|[https://rc.dv/reference/rc/cache](https://rc.dv/reference/rc/cache)
M|3.10|**Im|md (faster rp times)**
M|3.10|tx|Use nx.js's `after()` to schedule work that shd execute after a rp is sent. This prevents logging, an, and other side effects from blocking the rp.
M|3.10|**In|blocks rp**
M|3.10|tx|```tsx
M|3.10|tx|import { logUserAction } from '@/app/utils'
M|3.10|expo|Request) {
M|3.10|tx|// Perform mutation
M|3.10|tx|await updateDatabase(request)
M|3.10|tx|// Logging blocks the rp
M|3.10|tx|const userAgent = request.headers.get('us-ag') \|\| 'unknown'
M|3.10|tx|await logUserAction({ userAgent })
M|3.10|retu|'sc' }), {
M|3.10|stat|200,
M|3.10|head|{ 'cn-tp': 'application/json' }
M|3.10|tx|})
M|3.10|tx|}
M|3.10|tx|```
M|3.10|**Co|non-blocking**
M|3.10|tx|```tsx
M|3.10|tx|import { after } from 'nx/server'
M|3.10|tx|import { headers, cookies } from 'nx/headers'
M|3.10|tx|import { logUserAction } from '@/app/utils'
M|3.10|expo|Request) {
M|3.10|tx|// Perform mutation
M|3.10|tx|await updateDatabase(request)
M|3.10|tx|// Log after rp is sent
M|3.10|tx|after(async () => {
M|3.10|tx|const userAgent = (await headers()).get('us-ag') \|\| 'unknown'
M|3.10|tx|const sessionCookie = (await cookies()).get('sn-id')?.value \|\| 'anonymous'
M|3.10|tx|logUserAction({ sessionCookie, userAgent })
M|3.10|tx|})
M|3.10|retu|'sc' }), {
M|3.10|stat|200,
M|3.10|head|{ 'cn-tp': 'application/json' }
M|3.10|tx|})
M|3.10|tx|}
M|3.10|tx|```
M|3.10|tx|The rp is sent immediately while logging happens in the background.
M|3.10|**Co|**
M|3.10|it|an tracking
M|3.10|it|Audit logging
M|3.10|it|Sending notifications
M|3.10|it|Cache invalidation
M|3.10|it|Cleanup tasks
M|3.10|**Im|**
M|3.10|it|`after()` runs even if the rp fails or redirects
M|3.10|it|Works in Server Actions, rt Handlers, and Server cp
M|3.10|Refe|[https://nx.org/doc/app/ap-reference/functions/after](https://nx.org/doc/app/ap-reference/functions/after)
M|3.10|tx|---
M|4. C|**Im|md-hi**
M|4. C|tx|Automatic deduplication and efficient data fetching patterns reduce redundant network requests.
M|4.1 |**Im|lo (single listener for N cp)**
M|4.1 |tx|Use `useSWRSubscription()` to share global event listeners across cp instances.
M|4.1 |**In|N instances = N listeners**
M|4.1 |tx|```tsx
M|4.1 |func|string, callback: () => void) {
M|4.1 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|4.1 |cons|KeyboardEvent) => {
M|4.1 |tx|if (e.metaKey && e.key === key) {
M|4.1 |tx|callback()
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|window.addEventListener('keydown', handler)
M|4.1 |tx|return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handler)
M|4.1 |tx|}, [key, callback])
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|```
M|4.1 |tx|When using the `useKeyboardShortcut` hook multiple times, each instance will register a new listener.
M|4.1 |**Co|N instances = 1 listener**
M|4.1 |tx|```tsx
M|4.1 |tx|import useSWRSubscription from 'swr/subscription'
M|4.1 |tx|// md-level Map to track callbacks per key
M|4.1 |tx|const keyCallbacks = new Map<string, Set<() => void>>()
M|4.1 |func|string, callback: () => void) {
M|4.1 |tx|// Register this callback in the Map
M|4.1 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|4.1 |tx|if (!keyCallbacks.has(key)) {
M|4.1 |tx|keyCallbacks.set(key, new Set())
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|keyCallbacks.get(key)!.add(callback)
M|4.1 |tx|return () => {
M|4.1 |tx|const set = keyCallbacks.get(key)
M|4.1 |tx|if (set) {
M|4.1 |tx|set.dl(callback)
M|4.1 |tx|if (set.size === 0) {
M|4.1 |tx|keyCallbacks.dl(key)
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|}, [key, callback])
M|4.1 |tx|useSWRSubscription('global-keydown', () => {
M|4.1 |cons|KeyboardEvent) => {
M|4.1 |tx|if (e.metaKey && keyCallbacks.has(e.key)) {
M|4.1 |tx|keyCallbacks.get(e.key)!.forEach(cb => cb())
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|window.addEventListener('keydown', handler)
M|4.1 |tx|return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handler)
M|4.1 |tx|})
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|fn Profile() {
M|4.1 |tx|// Multiple shortcuts will share the same listener
M|4.1 |tx|useKeyboardShortcut('p', () => { /* ... */ })
M|4.1 |tx|useKeyboardShortcut('k', () => { /* ... */ })
M|4.1 |tx|// ...
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|```
M|4.2 |**Im|md (eliminates scroll delay caused by event listeners)**
M|4.2 |Add |true }` to touch and wheel event listeners to enable immediate scrolling. Browsers normally wait for listeners to finish to check if `preventDefault()` is called, causing scroll delay.
M|4.2 |**In|**
M|4.2 |tx|```ts
M|4.2 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|4.2 |cons|TouchEvent) => console.log(e.touches[0].clientX)
M|4.2 |cons|WheelEvent) => console.log(e.deltaY)
M|4.2 |tx|document.addEventListener('touchstart', handleTouch)
M|4.2 |tx|document.addEventListener('wheel', handleWheel)
M|4.2 |tx|return () => {
M|4.2 |tx|document.removeEventListener('touchstart', handleTouch)
M|4.2 |tx|document.removeEventListener('wheel', handleWheel)
M|4.2 |tx|}
M|4.2 |tx|}, [])
M|4.2 |tx|```
M|4.2 |**Co|**
M|4.2 |tx|```ts
M|4.2 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|4.2 |cons|TouchEvent) => console.log(e.touches[0].clientX)
M|4.2 |cons|WheelEvent) => console.log(e.deltaY)
M|4.2 |docu|true })
M|4.2 |docu|true })
M|4.2 |tx|return () => {
M|4.2 |tx|document.removeEventListener('touchstart', handleTouch)
M|4.2 |tx|document.removeEventListener('wheel', handleWheel)
M|4.2 |tx|}
M|4.2 |tx|}, [])
M|4.2 |tx|```
M|4.2 |**Us|** tracking/an, logging, any listener that doesn't call `preventDefault()`.
M|4.2 |**Do|** implementing custom swipe gestures, custom zoom controls, or any listener that needs `preventDefault()`.
M|4.3 |**Im|md-hi (automatic deduplication)**
M|4.3 |tx|SWR enables request deduplication, caching, and revalidation across cp instances.
M|4.3 |**In|no deduplication, each instance fetches**
M|4.3 |tx|```tsx
M|4.3 |tx|fn UserList() {
M|4.3 |tx|const [us, setUsers] = useState([])
M|4.3 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|4.3 |tx|fetch('/ap/us')
M|4.3 |tx|.then(r => r.json())
M|4.3 |tx|.then(setUsers)
M|4.3 |tx|}, [])
M|4.3 |tx|}
M|4.3 |tx|```
M|4.3 |**Co|multiple instances share one request**
M|4.3 |tx|```tsx
M|4.3 |tx|import useSWR from 'swr'
M|4.3 |tx|fn UserList() {
M|4.3 |cons|us } = useSWR('/ap/us', fetcher)
M|4.3 |tx|}
M|4.3 |tx|```
M|4.3 |**Fo|**
M|4.3 |tx|```tsx
M|4.3 |tx|import { useImmutableSWR } from '@/lib/swr'
M|4.3 |tx|fn StaticContent() {
M|4.3 |tx|const { data } = useImmutableSWR('/ap/config', fetcher)
M|4.3 |tx|}
M|4.3 |tx|```
M|4.3 |**Fo|**
M|4.3 |tx|```tsx
M|4.3 |tx|import { useSWRMutation } from 'swr/mutation'
M|4.3 |tx|fn UpdateButton() {
M|4.3 |tx|const { trigger } = useSWRMutation('/ap/us', updateUser)
M|4.3 |tx|return <button onClick={() => trigger()}>up</button>
M|4.3 |tx|}
M|4.3 |tx|```
M|4.3 |Refe|[https://swr.vc.app](https://swr.vc.app)
M|4.4 |**Im|md (prevents sc conflicts, reduces storage size)**
M|4.4 |tx|Add version prefix to keys and store only needed fields. Prevents sc conflicts and accidental storage of sensitive data.
M|4.4 |**In|**
M|4.4 |tx|```ts
M|4.4 |tx|// No version, stores everything, no er handling
M|4.4 |tx|localStorage.setItem('userConfig', JSON.stringify(fullUserObject))
M|4.4 |tx|const data = localStorage.getItem('userConfig')
M|4.4 |tx|```
M|4.4 |**Co|**
M|4.4 |tx|```ts
M|4.4 |tx|const VERSION = 'v2'
M|4.4 |func|{ theme: string; language: string }) {
M|4.4 |tx|try {
M|4.4 |loca|${VERSION}`, JSON.stringify(config))
M|4.4 |tx|} catch {
M|4.4 |tx|// Throws in incognito/private browsing, quota exceeded, or disabled
M|4.4 |tx|}
M|4.4 |tx|}
M|4.4 |tx|fn loadConfig() {
M|4.4 |tx|try {
M|4.4 |cons|${VERSION}`)
M|4.4 |retu|null
M|4.4 |tx|} catch {
M|4.4 |tx|return null
M|4.4 |tx|}
M|4.4 |tx|}
M|4.4 |tx|// Migration from v1 to v2
M|4.4 |tx|fn mg() {
M|4.4 |tx|try {
M|4.4 |cons|v1')
M|4.4 |tx|if (v1) {
M|4.4 |tx|const old = JSON.parse(v1)
M|4.4 |save|old.darkMode ? 'dark' : 'light', language: old.lang })
M|4.4 |loca|v1')
M|4.4 |tx|}
M|4.4 |tx|} catch {}
M|4.4 |tx|}
M|4.4 |tx|```
M|4.4 |**St|**
M|4.4 |tx|```ts
M|4.4 |tx|// us object has 20+ fields, only store what UI needs
M|4.4 |func|FullUser) {
M|4.4 |tx|try {
M|4.4 |loca|v1', JSON.stringify({
M|4.4 |them|us.preferences.theme,
M|4.4 |noti|us.preferences.notifications
M|4.4 |tx|}))
M|4.4 |tx|} catch {}
M|4.4 |tx|}
M|4.4 |tx|```
M|4.4 |**Al|** `getItem()` and `setItem()` throw in incognito/private browsing (Safari, Firefox), when quota exceeded, or when disabled.
M|4.4 |**Be|** sc evolution via versioning, reduced storage size, prevents storing tk/PII/internal flags.
M|4.4 |tx|---
M|5. R|**Im|md**
M|5. R|tx|Reducing unnecessary re-renders minimizes wasted computation and improves UI responsiveness.
M|5.1 |**Im|md (avoids redundant renders and state drift)**
M|5.1 |tx|If a value can be computed from current props/state, do not store it in state or up it in an effect. Derive it during render to avoid extra renders and state drift. Do not set state in effects solely in rp to prop changes; prefer derived values or keyed resets instead.
M|5.1 |**In|redundant state and effect**
M|5.1 |tx|```tsx
M|5.1 |tx|fn Form() {
M|5.1 |tx|const [firstName, setFirstName] = useState('First')
M|5.1 |tx|const [lastName, setLastName] = useState('Last')
M|5.1 |tx|const [fullName, setFullName] = useState('')
M|5.1 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|5.1 |tx|setFullName(firstName + ' ' + lastName)
M|5.1 |tx|}, [firstName, lastName])
M|5.1 |tx|return <p>{fullName}</p>
M|5.1 |tx|}
M|5.1 |tx|```
M|5.1 |**Co|derive during render**
M|5.1 |tx|```tsx
M|5.1 |tx|fn Form() {
M|5.1 |tx|const [firstName, setFirstName] = useState('First')
M|5.1 |tx|const [lastName, setLastName] = useState('Last')
M|5.1 |tx|const fullName = firstName + ' ' + lastName
M|5.1 |tx|return <p>{fullName}</p>
M|5.1 |tx|}
M|5.1 |tx|```
M|5.1 |Refe|[https://rc.dv/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect](https://rc.dv/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect)
M|5.2 |**Im|md (avoids unnecessary subscriptions)**
M|5.2 |tx|Don't subscribe to dynamic state (searchParams, localStorage) if you only read it inside callbacks.
M|5.2 |**In|subscribes to all searchParams changes**
M|5.2 |tx|```tsx
M|5.2 |func|{ chatId: string }) {
M|5.2 |tx|const searchParams = useSearchParams()
M|5.2 |tx|const handleShare = () => {
M|5.2 |tx|const ref = searchParams.get('ref')
M|5.2 |tx|shareChat(chatId, { ref })
M|5.2 |tx|}
M|5.2 |tx|return <button onClick={handleShare}>Share</button>
M|5.2 |tx|}
M|5.2 |tx|```
M|5.2 |**Co|reads on demand, no subscription**
M|5.2 |tx|```tsx
M|5.2 |func|{ chatId: string }) {
M|5.2 |tx|const handleShare = () => {
M|5.2 |tx|const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search)
M|5.2 |tx|const ref = params.get('ref')
M|5.2 |tx|shareChat(chatId, { ref })
M|5.2 |tx|}
M|5.2 |tx|return <button onClick={handleShare}>Share</button>
M|5.2 |tx|}
M|5.2 |tx|```
M|5.3 |**Im|lo-md (wasted computation on every render)**
M|5.3 |tx|When an expression is simple (few logical or arithmetical operators) and has a primitive result tp (boolean, number, string), do not wrap it in `useMemo`.
M|5.3 |tx|Calling `useMemo` and comparing hook dependencies may consume more resources than the expression itself.
M|5.3 |**In|**
M|5.3 |tx|```tsx
M|5.3 |func|Props) {
M|5.3 |tx|const isLoading = useMemo(() => {
M|5.3 |tx|return us.isLoading \|\| notifications.isLoading
M|5.3 |tx|}, [us.isLoading, notifications.isLoading])
M|5.3 |tx|if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />
M|5.3 |tx|// return some markup
M|5.3 |tx|}
M|5.3 |tx|```
M|5.3 |**Co|**
M|5.3 |tx|```tsx
M|5.3 |func|Props) {
M|5.3 |tx|const isLoading = us.isLoading \|\| notifications.isLoading
M|5.3 |tx|if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />
M|5.3 |tx|// return some markup
M|5.3 |tx|}
M|5.3 |tx|```
M|5.4 |**Im|hi (prevents remount on every render)**
M|5.4 |tx|Defining a cp inside another cp creates a new cp tp on every render. rc sees a different cp each time and fully remounts it, destroying all state and DOM.
M|5.4 |tx|A common reason developers do this is to access parent variables w/o passing props. Always pass props instead.
M|5.4 |**In|remounts on every render**
M|5.4 |tx|```tsx
M|5.4 |tx|fn UserProfile({ us, theme }) {
M|5.4 |tx|// Defined inside to access `theme` - BAD
M|5.4 |tx|const Avatar = () => (
M|5.4 |tx|<img
M|5.4 |tx|src={us.avatarUrl}
M|5.4 |clas|'avatar-light'}
M|5.4 |tx|/>
M|5.4 |tx|)
M|5.4 |tx|// Defined inside to access `us` - BAD
M|5.4 |tx|const Stats = () => (
M|5.4 |tx|<div>
M|5.4 |tx|<span>{us.followers} followers</span>
M|5.4 |tx|<span>{us.posts} posts</span>
M|5.4 |tx|</div>
M|5.4 |tx|)
M|5.4 |tx|return (
M|5.4 |tx|<div>
M|5.4 |tx|<Avatar />
M|5.4 |tx|<Stats />
M|5.4 |tx|</div>
M|5.4 |tx|)
M|5.4 |tx|}
M|5.4 |tx|```
M|5.4 |tx|Every time `UserProfile` renders, `Avatar` and `Stats` are new cp tp. rc unmounts the old instances and mounts new ones, losing any internal state, running effects again, and recreating DOM nodes.
M|5.4 |**Co|pass props instead**
M|5.4 |tx|```tsx
M|5.4 |func|{ src: string; theme: string }) {
M|5.4 |tx|return (
M|5.4 |tx|<img
M|5.4 |tx|src={src}
M|5.4 |clas|'avatar-light'}
M|5.4 |tx|/>
M|5.4 |tx|)
M|5.4 |tx|}
M|5.4 |func|{ followers: number; posts: number }) {
M|5.4 |tx|return (
M|5.4 |tx|<div>
M|5.4 |tx|<span>{followers} followers</span>
M|5.4 |tx|<span>{posts} posts</span>
M|5.4 |tx|</div>
M|5.4 |tx|)
M|5.4 |tx|}
M|5.4 |tx|fn UserProfile({ us, theme }) {
M|5.4 |tx|return (
M|5.4 |tx|<div>
M|5.4 |tx|<Avatar src={us.avatarUrl} theme={theme} />
M|5.4 |tx|<Stats followers={us.followers} posts={us.posts} />
M|5.4 |tx|</div>
M|5.4 |tx|)
M|5.4 |tx|}
M|5.4 |tx|```
M|5.4 |**Sy|**
M|5.4 |it|Input fields lose focus on every keystroke
M|5.4 |it|Animations restart unexpectedly
M|5.4 |it|`useEffect` cleanup/setup runs on every parent render
M|5.4 |it|Scroll position resets inside the cp
M|5.5 |**Im|md (restores memoization by using a constant for default value)**
M|5.5 |tx|When memoized cp has a default value for some non-primitive optional parameter, such as an array, fn, or object, calling the cp w/o that parameter results in broken memoization. This is bc new value instances are created on every rerender, and they do not pass strict equality comparison in `memo()`.
M|5.5 |tx|To address this issue, extract the default value into a constant.
M|5.5 |**In|`onClick` has different values on every rerender**
M|5.5 |tx|```tsx
M|5.5 |cons|{ onClick?: () => void }) {
M|5.5 |tx|// ...
M|5.5 |tx|})
M|5.5 |tx|// Used w/o optional onClick
M|5.5 |tx|<UserAvatar />
M|5.5 |tx|```
M|5.5 |**Co|stable default value**
M|5.5 |tx|```tsx
M|5.5 |tx|const NOOP = () => {};
M|5.5 |cons|{ onClick?: () => void }) {
M|5.5 |tx|// ...
M|5.5 |tx|})
M|5.5 |tx|// Used w/o optional onClick
M|5.5 |tx|<UserAvatar />
M|5.5 |tx|```
M|5.6 |**Im|md (enables early returns)**
M|5.6 |tx|Extract expensive work into memoized cp to enable early returns before computation.
M|5.6 |**In|computes avatar even when loading**
M|5.6 |tx|```tsx
M|5.6 |func|Props) {
M|5.6 |tx|const avatar = useMemo(() => {
M|5.6 |tx|const id = computeAvatarId(us)
M|5.6 |tx|return <Avatar id={id} />
M|5.6 |tx|}, [us])
M|5.6 |tx|if (loading) return <Skeleton />
M|5.6 |tx|return <div>{avatar}</div>
M|5.6 |tx|}
M|5.6 |tx|```
M|5.6 |**Co|skips computation when loading**
M|5.6 |tx|```tsx
M|5.6 |cons|{ us: us }) {
M|5.6 |tx|const id = useMemo(() => computeAvatarId(us), [us])
M|5.6 |tx|return <Avatar id={id} />
M|5.6 |tx|})
M|5.6 |func|Props) {
M|5.6 |tx|if (loading) return <Skeleton />
M|5.6 |tx|return (
M|5.6 |tx|<div>
M|5.6 |tx|<UserAvatar us={us} />
M|5.6 |tx|</div>
M|5.6 |tx|)
M|5.6 |tx|}
M|5.6 |tx|```
M|5.6 |**No|** If your project has [rc Compiler](https://rc.dv/learn/rc-compiler) enabled, manual memoization w/ `memo()` and `useMemo()` is not necessary. The compiler automatically optimizes re-renders.
M|5.7 |**Im|lo (minimizes effect re-runs)**
M|5.7 |tx|Specify primitive dependencies instead of objects to minimize effect re-runs.
M|5.7 |**In|re-runs on any us field change**
M|5.7 |tx|```tsx
M|5.7 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|5.7 |tx|console.log(us.id)
M|5.7 |tx|}, [us])
M|5.7 |tx|```
M|5.7 |**Co|re-runs only when id changes**
M|5.7 |tx|```tsx
M|5.7 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|5.7 |tx|console.log(us.id)
M|5.7 |tx|}, [us.id])
M|5.7 |tx|```
M|5.7 |**Fo|**
M|5.7 |tx|```tsx
M|5.7 |// I|runs on width=767, 766, 765...
