M|5.15|**Im|md (avoids unnecessary re-renders on frequent updates)**
M|5.15|tx|When a value changes frequently and you don't want a re-render on every up (e.g., mouse trackers, intervals, transient flags), store it in `useRef` instead of `useState`. Keep cp state for UI; use refs for temporary DOM-adjacent values. Updating a ref does not trigger a re-render.
