M|6. R|**Im|md**
M|6. R|tx|Optimizing the rendering process reduces the work the browser needs to do.
M|6.1 |**Im|lo (enables hardware acceleration)**
M|6.1 |tx|Many browsers don't have hardware acceleration for CSS3 animations on SVG elements. Wrap SVG in a `<div>` and animate the wrapper instead.
M|6.1 |**In|animating SVG directly - no hardware acceleration**
M|6.1 |tx|```tsx
M|6.1 |tx|fn LoadingSpinner() {
M|6.1 |tx|return (
M|6.1 |tx|<svg
M|6.1 |tx|className="animate-spin"
M|6.1 |tx|width="24"
M|6.1 |tx|height="24"
M|6.1 |tx|viewBox="0 0 24 24"
M|6.1 |tx|>
M|6.1 |tx|<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" />
M|6.1 |tx|</svg>
M|6.1 |tx|)
M|6.1 |tx|}
M|6.1 |tx|```
M|6.1 |**Co|animating wrapper div - hardware accelerated**
M|6.1 |tx|```tsx
M|6.1 |tx|fn LoadingSpinner() {
M|6.1 |tx|return (
M|6.1 |tx|<div className="animate-spin">
M|6.1 |tx|<svg
M|6.1 |tx|width="24"
M|6.1 |tx|height="24"
M|6.1 |tx|viewBox="0 0 24 24"
M|6.1 |tx|>
M|6.1 |tx|<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" />
M|6.1 |tx|</svg>
M|6.1 |tx|</div>
M|6.1 |tx|)
M|6.1 |tx|}
M|6.1 |tx|```
M|6.1 |tx|This applies to all CSS transforms and transitions (`transform`, `opacity`, `translate`, `scale`, `rotate`). The wrapper div allows browsers to use GPU acceleration for smoother animations.
M|6.2 |**Im|hi (faster initial render)**
M|6.2 |Appl|auto` to defer off-screen rendering.
M|6.2 |**CS|**
M|6.2 |tx|```css
M|6.2 |tx|.message-item {
M|6.2 |cont|auto;
M|6.2 |cont|0 80px;
M|6.2 |tx|}
M|6.2 |tx|```
M|6.2 |**Ex|**
M|6.2 |tx|```tsx
M|6.2 |func|{ messages: Message[] }) {
M|6.2 |tx|return (
M|6.2 |tx|<div className="overflow-y-auto h-screen">
M|6.2 |tx|{messages.map(msg => (
M|6.2 |tx|<div key={msg.id} className="message-item">
M|6.2 |tx|<Avatar us={msg.author} />
M|6.2 |tx|<div>{msg.cn}</div>
M|6.2 |tx|</div>
