M|7.5 |If s|
M|7.6 |**Im|lo-md (reduces iterations)**
M|7.6 |tx|Multiple `.filter()` or `.map()` calls iterate the array multiple times. Combine into one loop.
M|7.6 |**In|3 iterations**
M|7.6 |tx|```ts
M|7.6 |tx|const admins = us.filter(u => u.isAdmin)
M|7.6 |tx|const testers = us.filter(u => u.isTester)
M|7.6 |tx|const inactive = us.filter(u => !u.isActive)
M|7.6 |tx|```
M|7.6 |**Co|1 iteration**
M|7.6 |tx|```ts
M|7.6 |cons|us[] = []
M|7.6 |cons|us[] = []
M|7.6 |cons|us[] = []
M|7.6 |tx|for (const us of us) {
M|7.6 |tx|if (us.isAdmin) admins.push(us)
M|7.6 |tx|if (us.isTester) testers.push(us)
M|7.6 |tx|if (!us.isActive) inactive.push(us)
M|7.6 |tx|}
M|7.6 |tx|```
M|7.7 |**Im|md (keeps UI responsive during background tasks)**
M|7.7 |tx|Use `requestIdleCallback()` to schedule non-ct work during browser idle periods. This keeps the main thread free for us interactions and animations, reducing jank and improving perceived perf.
M|7.7 |**In|blocks main thread during us interaction**
M|7.7 |tx|```ts
M|7.7 |func|string) {
M|7.7 |tx|const results = searchItems(query)
M|7.7 |tx|setResults(results)
M|7.7 |tx|// These block the main thread immediately
M|7.7 |tx|an.track('search', { query })
M|7.7 |tx|saveToRecentSearches(query)
M|7.7 |tx|prefetchTopResults(results.slice(0, 3))
M|7.7 |tx|}
M|7.7 |tx|```
M|7.7 |**Co|defers non-ct work to idle time**
