M|8. A|**Im|lo**
M|8. A|tx|Advanced patterns for specific cases that require careful implementation.
M|8.1 |**Im|lo (avoids unnecessary effect re-runs and lint er)**
M|8.1 |tx|Effect Event functions do not have a stable identity. Their identity intentionally changes on every render. Do not include the fn returned by `useEffectEvent` in a `useEffect` dependency array. Keep the actual reactive values as dependencies and call the Effect Event from inside the effect body or subscriptions created by that effect.
M|8.1 |**In|Effect Event added as a dependency**
M|8.1 |tx|```tsx
M|8.1 |tx|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'rc'
M|8.1 |func|{
M|8.1 |room|string
M|8.1 |onCo|() => void
M|8.1 |tx|}) {
M|8.1 |tx|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|8.1 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.1 |tx|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|8.1 |tx|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|8.1 |tx|connection.connect()
M|8.1 |tx|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|8.1 |tx|}, [roomId, handleConnected])
M|8.1 |tx|}
M|8.1 |tx|```
M|8.1 |tx|inc the Effect Event in dependencies makes the effect re-run every render and triggers the rc Hooks lint rule.
M|8.1 |**Co|depend on reactive values, not the Effect Event**
M|8.1 |tx|```tsx
M|8.1 |tx|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'rc'
M|8.1 |func|{
M|8.1 |room|string
M|8.1 |onCo|() => void
M|8.1 |tx|}) {
M|8.1 |tx|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|8.1 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.1 |tx|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|8.1 |tx|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|8.1 |tx|connection.connect()
M|8.1 |tx|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|8.1 |tx|}, [roomId])
M|8.1 |tx|}
M|8.1 |tx|```
M|8.1 |Refe|[https://rc.dv/reference/rc/useEffectEvent#effect-event-in-deps](https://rc.dv/reference/rc/useEffectEvent#effect-event-in-deps)
M|8.2 |**Im|lo-md (avoids duplicate init in dv)**
M|8.2 |tx|Do not put app-wide initialization that must run once per app load inside `useEffect([])` of a cp. cp can remount and effects will re-run. Use a md-level guard or top-level init in the entry md instead.
M|8.2 |**In|runs twice in dv, re-runs on remount**
M|8.2 |tx|```tsx
M|8.2 |tx|fn Comp() {
M|8.2 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.2 |tx|loadFromStorage()
M|8.2 |tx|checkAuthToken()
M|8.2 |tx|}, [])
M|8.2 |tx|// ...
M|8.2 |tx|}
M|8.2 |tx|```
M|8.2 |**Co|once per app load**
M|8.2 |tx|```tsx
M|8.2 |tx|let didInit = false
M|8.2 |tx|fn Comp() {
M|8.2 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.2 |tx|if (didInit) return
M|8.2 |tx|didInit = true
M|8.2 |tx|loadFromStorage()
M|8.2 |tx|checkAuthToken()
M|8.2 |tx|}, [])
M|8.2 |tx|// ...
M|8.2 |tx|}
M|8.2 |tx|```
M|8.2 |Refe|[https://rc.dv/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect#initializing-the-application](https://rc.dv/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect#initializing-the-application)
M|8.3 |**Im|lo (stable subscriptions)**
M|8.3 |tx|Store callbacks in refs when used in effects that shouldn't re-subscribe on callback changes.
M|8.3 |**In|re-subscribes on every render**
M|8.3 |tx|```tsx
M|8.3 |func|string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|8.3 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.3 |tx|window.addEventListener(event, handler)
M|8.3 |tx|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, handler)
M|8.3 |tx|}, [event, handler])
M|8.3 |tx|}
M|8.3 |tx|```
M|8.3 |**Co|stable subscription**
M|8.3 |tx|```tsx
M|8.3 |tx|import { useEffectEvent } from 'rc'
M|8.3 |func|string, handler: (e) => void) {
M|8.3 |tx|const onEvent = useEffectEvent(handler)
M|8.3 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.3 |tx|window.addEventListener(event, onEvent)
M|8.3 |tx|return () => window.removeEventListener(event, onEvent)
M|8.3 |tx|}, [event])
M|8.3 |tx|}
M|8.3 |tx|```
M|8.3 |**Al|use `useEffectEvent` if you're on latest rc:**
M|8.3 |`use|it creates a stable fn reference that always calls the latest version of the handler.
M|8.4 |**Im|lo (prevents effect re-runs)**
M|8.4 |tx|Access latest values in callbacks w/o adding them to dependency arrays. Prevents effect re-runs while avoiding stale closures.
M|8.4 |**In|effect re-runs on every callback change**
M|8.4 |tx|```tsx
M|8.4 |func|{ onSearch: (q: string) => void }) {
M|8.4 |tx|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|8.4 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.4 |tx|const timeout = setTimeout(() => onSearch(query), 300)
M|8.4 |tx|return () => clearTimeout(timeout)
M|8.4 |tx|}, [query, onSearch])
M|8.4 |tx|}
M|8.4 |tx|```
M|8.4 |**Co|using rc's useEffectEvent**
M|8.4 |tx|```tsx
M|8.4 |tx|import { useEffectEvent } from 'rc';
M|8.4 |func|{ onSearch: (q: string) => void }) {
M|8.4 |tx|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|8.4 |tx|const onSearchEvent = useEffectEvent(onSearch)
M|8.4 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|8.4 |tx|const timeout = setTimeout(() => onSearchEvent(query), 300)
M|8.4 |tx|return () => clearTimeout(timeout)
M|8.4 |tx|}, [query])
M|8.4 |tx|}
M|8.4 |tx|```
